<BaseLayout
  title="Sources & References"
  description="ANU Wiki data sources — ANU official publications, Australian Government education data, and academic references."
>
  <article class="article-body">
    <div class="prose">
      <h1>Sources & References</h1>
      <p>ANU Wiki articles are based on the following public data and academic sources. Individual article-level citations are included at the end of each article.</p>

      <h2>ANU Official Sources</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>ANU Official Website</strong> — anu.edu.au · Course catalogues, academic policies, campus services</li>
        <li><strong>ANU Academic Colleges</strong> — College of Arts & Social Sciences, College of Asia & the Pacific, College of Business & Economics, College of Engineering & Computer Science, College of Health & Medicine, College of Law, College of Science</li>
        <li><strong>ANU Library</strong> — anulib.anu.edu.au · Research databases, past exam papers</li>
        <li><strong>ANU Residential Halls</strong> — Accommodation services and residential life</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Australian Government</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Department of Education</strong> — education.gov.au · Higher education policy, QILT surveys</li>
        <li><strong>Department of Home Affairs</strong> — homeaffairs.gov.au · Student visa requirements</li>
        <li><strong>Study Australia</strong> — studyaustralia.gov.au · Official international student portal</li>
        <li><strong>TEQSA</strong> — teqsa.gov.au · Tertiary education quality assurance</li>
        <li><strong>Australian Bureau of Statistics (ABS)</strong> — abs.gov.au · Education and demographic statistics</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Academic Resources</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Australian Universities' Review</strong> — Higher education research and policy analysis</li>
        <li><strong>Journal of Higher Education Policy and Management</strong> — Tertiary education administration</li>
        <li><strong>Good Universities Guide</strong> — University rankings and ratings data</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
